{"title_page": "Jeremy Koling", "text_new": "{{Infobox disc golfer\n| name              = Jeremy Koling\n| image             = \n| image_size        = <!-- e.g. 250px (default is 200px) -->\n| caption           = \n| fullname          = Jeremy Koling\n| nickname          = \n| birth_date        = October 2, 1985\n| birth_place       = [[Charlotte, NC]]\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| death_place       = \n| height            = 6 ft 6 in\n| weight            = 230 lbs\n| nationality       = {{USA}}\n| residence         = [[Charlotte, NC]]\n| spouse            = \n| partner           = \n| children          = \n| college           = \n| status            = Professional\n| yearpro           = 2009\n| retired           = <!-- Year retired -->\n| tour              = PDGA National Tour <br/> Disc Golf Pro Tour\n| extour            = <!-- Former tours which a member of -->\n| prowins           = 64\n| pdgawins          = 2\n| dgwtwins          = 1\n| dgptwins          = 2\n| worlds            = 11th: 2012\n| usdgc             = '''Won''': 2016\n| aussie            = \n| euromast          = 5th: 2015\n| euroopen         =3rd: 2015\n| japan               =\n| dghofyear         = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame year inducted -->\n| award1            = PDGA Male Rookie of the Year\n| year1             = 2009\n| award2            = Disc Golf World Tour Champion\n| year2             = 2016\n|award3             = \n| year3             = \n| award4            = \n| year4             = \n| awardssection     = <!-- location of awards page or section -->\n}}\n\n'''Jeremy Koling''' is a professional [[disc golf]]er from Charlotte, North Carolina. He competes on the sport's two main tours: the PDGA National Tour, and Disc Golf Pro Tour. Among his most notable accomplishments are his 2008 PDGA Amateur World Championship win and his 2016 [[United States Disc Golf Championship]] win.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discgolfworldtour.com/usdgc-round-4-gets-cancelled-koling-new-us-dgwt-champion-wysocki-wins-dgwt-points-title/ |title=USDGC 2016 Event, Tour & Points Winners}}</ref> Koling is the only male player to win the PDGA Amateur World Championships and earn the PDGA Male Rookie of the Year Award in back-to-back years (2008 and 2009).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pdga.com/awards|title=PDGA Award Winners and World Champions}}</ref> \nAdditionally, Koling became the first and only player to win a PDGA Major at both the amateur and professional level after his 2016 USDGC win. Koling has also won at every tier available in amateur and professional divisions throughout his career. Jeremy loves spending time with his new found friends the Wilkinsons. What a quarantine Zoom 40th birthday celebration it was!\n\n\n==  Professional career ==\n\nKoling has 68 professional wins. As a professional, he has won two National Tour events and one Major, the 2016 USDGC. He finished 4th in the 2016 NT,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pdga.com/national-tour/2016/standings#men |title=2016 National Tour Elite Series Standings}}</ref> and 16th in the inaugural DGPT points standings. He has won two Pro World Mixed Doubles Championships with partner [[Paige Pierce]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pdga.com/player/33705 |title=PDGA Player Page: Jeremy Koling}}</ref>\n\n=== Notable wins ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!|Year ||Tournament || Tier || Stroke Margin ||Winning Score ||Runner Up||Prize Money\n|-\n|2008|| PDGA Amateur World Championship|| Am-'''M''' || align=\"center\" |-12 || (53-64-55-51-52-54-49-49-32=459)|| Ryan Herzog || -\n|-\n|2014|| [[Maple Hill Open]] || NT|| align=\"center\"|-1 || -17 (57-56-57-53=223) || [[Richard Wysocki]] || $2,500\n|-\n|2015|| Memorial Championship || NT || align=\"center\"|Playoff || -41  (43-50-46-47=186) || [[Paul McBeth]] ||$5,000\n|-\n|2016||[[United States Disc Golf Championship]]|| '''M''' || align=\"center\"| -4 || -17 (61-59-60=180) || [[Nikko Locastro]] || $10,000\n|-\n|2017|| Waco Annual Charity Open || DGPT || align=\"center\"|Playoff || -34  (54-58-55=167) || James Conrad ||$2,810\n|-\n|2018\n|Waco Annual Charity Open\n|DGPT\n|Playoff\n|\n|Nate Perkins\n|$3,000\n|}\n\n===Summary===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Competition Tier ||Wins || 2nd || 3rd ||Top-5 ||Top-25 || Events*\n|-\n|World Championships || 0 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 6 || 7\n|-\n|Other Majors || 1 || 0 || 1 || 3 || 12 || 16\n|-\n|National Tour || 2 || 0 || 1 || 9 || 40 || 44\n|}\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Through January 2017\n\n===Annual statistics===\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!|Year || Events || Wins || Top 3 || Earnings || $ / Event || Rating<sup>\u2020</sup>||World<br/>Rankings<sup>\u2020</sup>\n|-\n|2007 || align=\"right\"|1 || align=\"right\"|0 || align=\"right\"|0 || align=\"right\"|$0|| align=\"right\"|$0 || align=\"right\"|968 || align=center|-\n|-\n|2008 || align=\"right\"|22 || align=\"right\"|3 || align=\"right\"|7 || align=\"right\"|$1,683 || align=\"right\"|$76.50 || align=\"right\"|995|| align=center|-\n|-\n|2009 || align=\"right\"|26 || align=\"right\"|7 || align=\"right\"|14 || align=\"right\"|$6,894 || align=\"right\"|$265.15 || align=\"right\"|1005|| align=center|38\n|-\n|2010 || align=\"right\"|32 || align=\"right\"|6 || align=\"right\"|15 || align=\"right\"|$11,315 || align=\"right\"|$353.59 || align=\"right\"|1019|| align=center|28\n|-\n|2011 || align=\"right\"|38 || align=\"right\"|14 || align=\"right\"|21 || align=\"right\"|$13,298 || align=\"right\"|$349.95 || align=\"right\"|1023|| align=center|21\n|-\n|2012 || align=\"right\"|38 || align=\"right\"|9 || align=\"right\"|23 || align=\"right\"|$15,093 || align=\"right\"|$397.18 || align=\"right\"|1029|| align=center|14\n|-\n|2013 || align=\"right\"|33 || align=\"right\"|5 || align=\"right\"|10 || align=\"right\"|$15,814 || align=\"right\"|$479.21 || align=\"right\"|1027|| align=center|22\n|-\n|2014 || align=\"right\"|32 || align=\"right\"|10 || align=\"right\"|17 || align=\"right\"|$19,993 || align=\"right\"|$