f; font-weight:bold; background:#069; padding:0.3em;\" | 1988\n! style=\"color:#fff; font-weight:bold; background:#069; padding:0.3em;\" | 1989\n! style=\"color:#fff; font-weight:bold; background:#069; padding:0.3em;\" | Total\n|-\n|13\n|52\n|57\n|48\n|42\n|19\n|14\n|18\n|36\n|40\n|25\n|11\n|12\n|10\n|11\n|17\n\n|10\n|10\n|1\n|446\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Aviation|United States}}\n{{aircontent\n|related=\n* [[McDonnell Douglas KC-10 Extender]]\n* [[McDonnell Douglas MD-11]]\n|similar aircraft=\n* [[Boeing 747SP]]\n* [[Boeing 767]]\n* [[Lockheed L-1011 TriStar]]\n* [[Airbus A300]]\n* [[Ilyushin Il-86]]\n|lists=\n* [[List of jet airliners]]\n|see also=\n}}\n\n==References==\n\n===Citations===\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{Refbegin}}\n* Endres, G\u00fcnter. ''McDonnell Douglas DC-10''. St. Paul, Minnesota: MBI Publishing Company, 1998. {{ISBN|0-7603-0617-6}}.\n* Fielder, J.H. and D. Birsch. [https://books.google.com/books?id=gBHGmwmMj30C ''The DC-10 Case: A Study in Applied Ethics, Technology, and Society'']. Albany, New York: SUNY Press, 1992. {{ISBN|0-7914-1087-0}}.\n* Kocivar, Ben. [https://books.google.com/books?id=-AAAAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA50 \"Giant Tri-Jets Are Coming\"]. ''Popular Science'', December 1970, pp.&nbsp;50\u201352, 116. ISSN 0161-7370.\n* Porter, Andrew. \"Transatlantic Betrayal \" The RB211 and the Demise of Rolls-Royce LTD. Stroud. UK. Amberley, 2013. {{ISBN|978-1-4456-0649-1}}\n* Steffen, Arthur, A. C. ''McDonnell Douglas DC-10 and KC-10 Extender''. Hinckley, Leicester, UK: Aerofax, 1998. {{ISBN|1-85780-051-6}}.\n* Waddington, Terry. ''McDonnell Douglas DC-10''. Miami, Florida: World Transport Press, 2000. {{ISBN|1-892437-04-X}}.\n* \"World Airliner Census\". ''Flight International'', Volume 184, Number 5403, August 13\u201319, 2013, pp.&nbsp;40\u201358.\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons|McDonnell Douglas DC-10}}\n* [http://www.boeing.com/history/products/dc-10.page DC-10/KC-10 history on Boeing.com]\n* {{cite web |u